hints.description: This global company is a leading provider of paper and packaging solutions, serving a wide range of industries including food and beverage, consumer goods, and industrial markets. They manufacture containerboard, corrugated packaging, and specialty paper products, focusing on sustainable practices and innovative solutions for their customers. The merger of two major players in 2022 created a powerhouse in the packaging sector, led by CEO Hugh Kelly.
hints.funFact1: Before the merger, one of the companies that now forms ***** was originally founded in 1934 by Robert P. ***** as a small paper bag company in Kalamazoo, Michigan. It quickly expanded, becoming a significant player in the paper industry.
hints.funFact2: ***** operates over 350 facilities across 30 countries, employing approximately 48,000 people worldwide, demonstrating its truly global reach and impact on the packaging supply chain.
